{
  "texts": [
    "Going forward, it is imperative for future research to adeptly navigate the complexities presented by class imbalances and to employ evaluation metrics that more accurately capture the true performance of models, particularly in fields as sensitive as mental health diagnostics.",
    "[46] [47] [48] [49] In a comparison between our lightweight multitask models and large language models (LLMs) like ChatGPT, GPT-4, and LLaMA, our models outperform general LLMs.",
    "Exceptions are MentalLLaMA 7B and MentalLLaMA-Chat 7B, trained specifically on mental health data, achieving slightly better F1 scores.",
    "However, these gains come at the cost of significant training effort, expert data curation, and substantial resources.",
    "General LLMs, trained on broad datasets, may lack nuanced expert knowledge, and fine-tuning them requires a large amount of domain-specific data, challenging in fields with data scarcity like mental health."
  ]
}